# Entity Guidelines

## 🚨 CRITICAL: Entity Module Ownership Rules

### One Entity Per Module
- **Every entity must be owned by exactly one feature module**
- **Do not import or use entities from other modules**
- **Use services for cross-module communication**
- **Create dedicated entities if similar data structures are needed**
- **Exception**: Only `AbstractEntity` and entities in `src/common/` can be shared

### Example: Correct Entity Organization
```
modules/user/
├── user.entity.ts          ✅ Owned by user module
└── user-settings.entity.ts ✅ Owned by user module

modules/post/
├── post.entity.ts          ✅ Owned by post module
└── post-category.entity.ts ✅ Owned by post module

// ❌ WRONG: Don't do this
modules/post/
├── post.entity.ts
└── user.entity.ts          ❌ User entity belongs to user module

// ✅ CORRECT: Use services for cross-module data
@Injectable()
export class PostService {
  constructor(
    private userService: UserService, // ✅ Use service, not entity
  ) {}
}
```

## Entity Structure Pattern

```ts
import { Column, Entity, OneToMany, OneToOne, VirtualColumn } from 'typeorm';

import { AbstractEntity } from '../../common/abstract.entity.ts';
import { RoleType } from '../../constants/role-type.ts';
import { UseDto } from '../../decorators/use-dto.decorator.ts';
// NOTE: TypeORM relation decorators require referencing the related entity class.
// This is the ONLY exception to the "no cross-module entity imports" rule.
// Do NOT use PostEntity anywhere else in the user module outside of this relation.
import { PostEntity } from '../post/post.entity.ts';
import type { UserDtoOptions } from './dtos/user.dto.ts';
import { UserDto } from './dtos/user.dto.ts';
import { UserSettingsEntity } from './user-settings.entity.ts';

@Entity({ name: 'users' })
@UseDto(UserDto)
export class UserEntity extends AbstractEntity<UserDto, UserDtoOptions> {
  @Column({ nullable: true, type: 'varchar' })
  firstName!: string | null;

  @Column({ nullable: true, type: 'varchar' })
  lastName!: string | null;

  @Column({ type: 'enum', enum: RoleType, default: RoleType.USER })
  role!: RoleType;

  @Column({ unique: true, nullable: true, type: 'varchar' })
  email!: string | null;

  @Column({ nullable: true, type: 'varchar' })
  password!: string | null;

  @Column({ nullable: true, type: 'varchar' })
  phone!: string | null;

  @Column({ nullable: true, type: 'varchar' })
  avatar!: string | null;

  @VirtualColumn({
    query: (alias) =>
      `SELECT CONCAT(${alias}.first_name, ' ', ${alias}.last_name)`,
  })
  fullName!: string;

  @OneToOne(() => UserSettingsEntity, (userSettings) => userSettings.user)
  settings?: UserSettingsEntity;

  @OneToMany(() => PostEntity, (postEntity) => postEntity.user)
  posts?: PostEntity[];
}
```

## Entity Best Practices

### 1. Base Entity Usage
- **Always extend `AbstractEntity`** for common fields (id, createdAt, updatedAt)
- Use `@UseDto()` decorator to link entity with its DTO
- Use explicit table names with `@Entity({ name: 'table_name' })`

### 2. Column Configuration
```ts
// ✅ Explicit column types
@Column({ type: 'varchar', length: 255 })
name!: string;

@Column({ type: 'int', default: 0 })
count!: number;

@Column({ type: 'boolean', default: false })
isActive!: boolean;

@Column({ type: 'timestamp', default: () => 'CURRENT_TIMESTAMP' })
createdAt!: Date;

@Column({ type: 'enum', enum: StatusType, default: StatusType.PENDING })
status!: StatusType;

// ❌ Avoid implicit types
@Column()
name!: string; // Type will be inferred, but better to be explicit
```

### 3. Nullable and Required Fields
```ts
// Required field (not nullable)
@Column({ type: 'varchar' })
email!: string;

// Nullable field
@Column({ nullable: true, type: 'varchar' })
firstName!: string | null;

// Optional with default
@Column({ type: 'boolean', default: false })
isVerified!: boolean;
```

### 4. Unique Constraints
```ts
// Single column unique
@Column({ unique: true, type: 'varchar' })
email!: string;

// Multiple column unique constraint
@Entity({ name: 'user_roles' })
@Unique(['userId', 'roleId'])
export class UserRoleEntity extends AbstractEntity {
  @Column({ type: 'uuid' })
  userId!: Uuid;

  @Column({ type: 'uuid' })
  roleId!: Uuid;
}
```

## Relationship Patterns

### One-to-One Relationships
```ts
// Owner side (has foreign key)
@Entity({ name: 'user_settings' })
export class UserSettingsEntity extends AbstractEntity {
  @Column({ type: 'uuid' })
  userId!: Uuid;

  @OneToOne(() => UserEntity, (user) => user.settings)
  @JoinColumn({ name: 'user_id' })
  user!: Relation<UserEntity>;

  @Column({ type: 'boolean', default: true })
  emailNotifications!: boolean;
}

// Inverse side (references the owner)
@Entity({ name: 'users' })
export class UserEntity extends AbstractEntity {
  @OneToOne(() => UserSettingsEntity, (settings) => settings.user)
  settings?: UserSettingsEntity;
}
```

### One-to-Many Relationships
```ts
// Parent side (one)
@Entity({ name: 'users' })
export class UserEntity extends AbstractEntity {
  @OneToMany(() => PostEntity, (post) => post.user)
  posts?: PostEntity[];
}

// Child side (many)
@Entity({ name: 'posts' })
export class PostEntity extends AbstractEntity {
  @Column({ type: 'uuid' })
  userId!: Uuid;

  @ManyToOne(() => UserEntity, (user) => user.posts, {
    onDelete: 'CASCADE',
    onUpdate: 'CASCADE',
  })
  @JoinColumn({ name: 'user_id' })
  user!: Relation<UserEntity>;
}
```

### Many-to-Many Relationships
```ts
// Using junction table entity (recommended for complex scenarios)
@Entity({ name: 'user_roles' })
export class UserRoleEntity extends AbstractEntity {
  @Column({ type: 'uuid' })
  userId!: Uuid;

  @Column({ type: 'uuid' })
  roleId!: Uuid;

  @ManyToOne(() => UserEntity, (user) => user.userRoles)
  @JoinColumn({ name: 'user_id' })
  user!: Relation<UserEntity>;

  @ManyToOne(() => RoleEntity, (role) => role.userRoles)
  @JoinColumn({ name: 'role_id' })
  role!: Relation<RoleEntity>;

  @Column({ type: 'timestamp', default: () => 'CURRENT_TIMESTAMP' })
  assignedAt!: Date;
}

// Simple many-to-many (for basic scenarios)
@Entity({ name: 'posts' })
export class PostEntity extends AbstractEntity {
  @ManyToMany(() => TagEntity, (tag) => tag.posts)
  @JoinTable({
    name: 'post_tags',
    joinColumn: { name: 'post_id', referencedColumnName: 'id' },
    inverseJoinColumn: { name: 'tag_id', referencedColumnName: 'id' },
  })
  tags?: TagEntity[];
}
```

## Virtual Columns and Computed Properties

```ts
@Entity({ name: 'users' })
export class UserEntity extends AbstractEntity {
  @Column({ type: 'varchar' })
  firstName!: string;

  @Column({ type: 'varchar' })
  lastName!: string;

  // Database-computed virtual column
  @VirtualColumn({
    query: (alias) =>
      `SELECT CONCAT(${alias}.first_name, ' ', ${alias}.last_name)`,
  })
  fullName!: string;

  // Application-computed getter (not in database)
  get displayName(): string {
    return `${this.firstName} ${this.lastName}`.trim();
  }
}
```

## Entity Subscribers

```ts
// entity-subscribers/user.subscriber.ts
import { EventSubscriber, EntitySubscriber, InsertEvent, UpdateEvent } from 'typeorm';
import { hash } from 'argon2';

import { UserEntity } from '../modules/user/user.entity.ts';

@EventSubscriber()
export class UserSubscriber implements EntitySubscriber<UserEntity> {
  listenTo() {
    return UserEntity;
  }

  async beforeInsert(event: InsertEvent<UserEntity>) {
    if (event.entity.password) {
      event.entity.password = await hash(event.entity.password);
    }
  }

  async beforeUpdate(event: UpdateEvent<UserEntity>) {
    if (event.entity?.password) {
      event.entity.password = await hash(event.entity.password);
    }
  }
}
```

## Indexing Guidelines

```ts
@Entity({ name: 'posts' })
@Index(['userId', 'createdAt']) // Composite index for common queries
@Index(['status']) // Single column index
export class PostEntity extends AbstractEntity {
  @Column({ type: 'uuid' })
  @Index() // Index on foreign key
  userId!: Uuid;

  @Column({ type: 'enum', enum: PostStatus })
  @Index() // Index on frequently queried enum
  status!: PostStatus;

  @Column({ type: 'varchar' })
  @Index('IDX_POST_TITLE_FULLTEXT', { fulltext: true }) // Full-text search index
  title!: string;
}
```

## Common Patterns

### Soft Delete
```ts
@Entity({ name: 'posts' })
export class PostEntity extends AbstractEntity {
  @DeleteDateColumn()
  deletedAt?: Date;

  // Custom soft delete methods
  softDelete(): void {
    this.deletedAt = new Date();
  }

  restore(): void {
    this.deletedAt = undefined;
  }

  get isDeleted(): boolean {
    return this.deletedAt !== undefined;
  }
}
```

### Audit Fields
```ts
@Entity({ name: 'posts' })
export class PostEntity extends AbstractEntity {
  @Column({ type: 'uuid', nullable: true })
  createdBy?: Uuid;

  @Column({ type: 'uuid', nullable: true })
  updatedBy?: Uuid;

  @ManyToOne(() => UserEntity)
  @JoinColumn({ name: 'created_by' })
  creator?: UserEntity;

  @ManyToOne(() => UserEntity)
  @JoinColumn({ name: 'updated_by' })
  updater?: UserEntity;
}
```

### Validation and Constraints
```ts
@Entity({ name: 'products' })
@Check('price > 0') // Database-level constraint
@Unique(['sku']) // Unique constraint
export class ProductEntity extends AbstractEntity {
  @Column({ type: 'varchar', length: 100 })
  @Length(1, 100) // Application-level validation
  name!: string;

  @Column({ type: 'decimal', precision: 10, scale: 2 })
  @IsPositive() // Application-level validation
  price!: number;

  @Column({ type: 'varchar', length: 50 })
  @Matches(/^[A-Z0-9-]+$/) // Custom pattern validation
  sku!: string;
}
```

## Best Practices Summary

1. **Entity Ownership**: One entity per module, no cross-module entity imports
2. **Base Classes**: Always extend `AbstractEntity`
3. **Table Names**: Use explicit table names in plural form
4. **Column Types**: Always specify explicit column types
5. **Relationships**: Use proper cascade options and `Relation<T>` type
6. **Indexes**: Add indexes for foreign keys and frequently queried columns
7. **Validation**: Use both database and application-level validation
8. **Documentation**: Use `@UseDto()` to link entities with DTOs
9. **Naming**: Use descriptive entity and column names
10. **Constraints**: Use database constraints for data integrity